%spark
/* extend spark sql */
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions.udf
import org.apache.spark.sql._

def zScore(value: Double, mean: Double, sd: Double): Double = {
    (value-mean)/sd
}

val rowZScore : (Double, Double, Double) => Double = zScore(_,_,_)

val zScoreFun = udf(rowZScore)

/*
// alternative to register for the sql world
spark.udf.register("zScore", (value: Double, mean: Double, sd: Double) => zScore(value, mean, sd))
*/

val zscoredata = Seq(2.0, 2.0, 2.0, 50.0, 50.0, 50.0, 75.0, 75.0, 120.0, 120.0, 250.0, 280.0).toDF("score")

zscoredata.createOrReplaceTempView("simple")

val results = spark.sql("select avg(score) as mean, stddev_pop(score) as sd from simple")

val meanSd = results.map { case Row(mean: Double, sd: Double) => (mean, sd) }.collect().head
val mean = meanSd._1
val sd = meanSd._2

/*
mean: 316.33
sd: 811.85
*/

zscoredata
  .withColumn("zscore", zScoreFun(col("score"), lit(mean), lit(sd)))
  .createOrReplaceTempView("zscores")
